OL,3,CSacred headdress returned from Exeter
OL,4,Cto Siksika Nation
OL,6,FA ceremonial woman's headdress which
OL,7,Fwas on display at a museum in Exeter
OL,8,Fhas been returned to the Siksika
OL,9,FNation where it was originally from.
OL,11,FThe clothing is made of buffalo horns,
OL,12,Fsacred bird feathers, porcupine
OL,13,Fquills, and adorned with red cloth and
OL,14,Fbrass bells.
OL,16,FA delegation from the Siksika Nation
OL,17,Ftravelled to Exeter to repatriate the
OL,18,Fsacred headdress to the Blackfoot
OL,19,Ftribe in a ceremony on 5 June at the
OL,20,FRoyal Albert Memorial Museum & Art
OL,21,FGallery (RAMM).
