OL,3,CSacred headdress returned from Exeter
OL,4,Cto Siksika Nation
OL,6,FJulien Parsons, RAMM's Collections &
OL,7,FContent Manager, said: "It was a
OL,8,Fmoving experience for all of us lucky
OL,9,Fenough to be present.
OL,11,F"The elders performed a short ceremony
OL,12,Fand then painstakingly bundled and
OL,13,Fwrapped the headdress in coloured
OL,14,Fcloth. It will travel like this back
OL,15,Fto Canada where it will return to its
OL,16,Fsacred use by the Siksika people."
OL,18,FThe ceremonial headdress was given to
OL,19,Fthe museum in 1920 by Edgar Dewdney, a
OL,20,FLieutenant Governor of the Northwest
OL,21,FTerritories.
