OL,3,CSacred headdress returned from Exeter
OL,4,Cto Siksika Nation
OL,6,FResearch by Siksika Nation, in
OL,7,Fcollaboration with Kainai and
OL,8,FBlackfeet Nations, identified the
OL,9,Fheaddress as a sacred ceremonial item,
OL,10,Fonce worn by a holy woman of the
OL,11,FBlackfoot Holy Buffalo Woman Society
OL,12,Fknown as the Motokiks.
OL,14,FIn 2022 a formal request was made for
OL,15,Fits repatriation.
OL,17,FJoset Melting Tallow, of the Siksika
OL,18,FNation, said: "The ceremonial Buffalo
OL,19,Fwoman's headdress holds immense sacred
OL,20,Fsignificance to the Blackfoot people.
