OL,3,CSacred headdress returned from Exeter
OL,4,Cto Siksika Nation
OL,6,F"Its return to Siksika Nation
OL,7,Fsymbolises not only the preservation
OL,8,Fof our cultural heritage, but also the
OL,9,Frecognition of our history and
OL,10,Ftraditions, and is a profound
OL,11,Ftestament to our ancestors' spiritual
OL,12,Fand cultural practices."
OL,14,FThe sacred bundle is being returned to
OL,15,Fthe Motokiks so that it can be used
OL,16,Fonce again by the holy women.
